#compdef gigapi
# =============================================================================
# gigapi — gigapi/gigapi's "GigAPI" — a Go
#   TIMESERIES LAKEHOUSE that ingests
#   InfluxDB Line Protocol or Parquet data,
#   stores it as hive-partitioned PARQUET
#   files on local FS / S3 / MinIO / GCS,
#   and serves QUERIES through both an HTTP
#   `/query` endpoint (DuckDB SQL) and a
#   FlightSQL gRPC server.  Built on direct
#   `apache/arrow-go/v18 v18.3.0` — the
#   CANONICAL Apache Arrow Go implementation
#   from the Apache Software Foundation
#   (formerly nested at apache/arrow,
#   extracted to a standalone module
#   apache/arrow-go since Arrow 18).  Go=109
#   leader bump continuing Axis 54 (Apache
#   Arrow Columnar Format) at the Go pole,
#   opened by R805 `_csv2arrow` (Rust=109,
#   arrow 58.1).
#
# AXIS 54 — APACHE ARROW COLUMNAR FORMAT — GO POLE
# =================================================
# `apache/arrow-go` is the OFFICIAL Apache
# Software Foundation Go implementation of
# the Apache Arrow columnar in-memory data
# format + IPC protocol + Flight RPC.
# Maintained under the Apache Arrow
# governance umbrella.  ~10.6k stars across
# the parent `apache/arrow` repo (~3.5k for
# the extracted `apache/arrow-go` module).
# Apache 2.0.  Provides:
#   - `arrow`            columnar in-memory
#                        type system +
#                        record batches
#   - `arrow/ipc`        IPC reader/writer
#                        (File + Stream
#                        variants)
#   - `arrow/flight`     Apache Arrow Flight
#                        gRPC over HTTP/2
#                        for streaming
#                        column batches
#   - `arrow/flightsql`  FlightSQL — Arrow
#                        Flight + a SQL
#                        sublanguage for
#                        OLAP query
#                        execution
#   - `arrow/csv`        CSV reader to
#                        Arrow record
#                        batches
#   - `arrow/parquet`    Parquet reader/
#                        writer
#                        integration
#
# Other Axis 54 implementations across the
# corpus:
#   * Rust       (R805): arrow 58.1
#                — bundled in `csv2arrow`
#                  (CSV → Arrow IPC
#                  converter)
#   * Go         (R806, THIS ROUND):
#                apache/arrow-go/v18 v18.3.0
#                — bundled in this round's
#                `gigapi` (timeseries
#                lakehouse exposing
#                FlightSQL + DuckDB SQL
#                over HTTP)
#   * TS-Node    (R807 will close):
#                apache-arrow npm — JS/TS
#                impl
#
# Distinguishing gigapi from sibling
# timeseries / lakehouse tooling:
#   - INFLUXDB v3 (`_influx`, in corpus):
#     closed-core (InfluxDB Cloud is the
#     hosted product).  gigapi is 100%
#     open-source, no opencore gimmicks
#     per upstream README
#   - VICTORIAMETRICS (`_vmctl`,
#     `_vmagent`, in corpus): operational
#     timeseries DB.  gigapi is a
#     lakehouse that uses Parquet as the
#     storage substrate (vs custom binary
#     format) for cheaper cold storage
#   - CLICKHOUSE (`_clickhouse-client`,
#     `_dozer` R801, `_clickhouse_sinker`
#     R802, `_hdx` R803, in corpus):
#     full OLAP database.  gigapi is the
#     specifically-timeseries-shaped
#     query-on-Parquet variant
#   - DUCKDB (`_duckdb`, in corpus):
#     embedded analytical SQL engine.
#     gigapi USES DuckDB internally as
#     the query engine but adds:
#       (a) HTTP `/query` server +
#           FlightSQL gRPC server
#       (b) InfluxDB Line Protocol
#           ingestion
#       (c) Hive-partitioned auto-
#           compaction
#       (d) S3 / MinIO / GCS object-
#           storage backend
#       (e) Hot-reload metadata
#           catalog (JSON or Redis)
#   - APACHE ICEBERG / DELTA LAKE /
#     APACHE HUDI: same data-lakehouse
#     concept but heavier (REST catalog,
#     metastore service, etc.).  gigapi
#     is the LIGHT timeseries-shaped
#     alternative
#
# KEY GIGAPI FEATURES:
#   - DUCKDB SQL + PARQUET STORAGE —
#     queries run on DuckDB's column-
#     oriented execution engine over
#     local + remote Parquet files.
#     Sub-second queries on TB-scale
#     timeseries
#   - FLIGHTSQL gRPC — clients in any
#     language with a FlightSQL driver
#     (Python flightsql-dbapi, JDBC
#     flightsql, etc.) can query gigapi
#     with native Arrow batches (no
#     CSV/JSON serialisation overhead)
#   - INFLUXDB LINE PROTOCOL INGESTION
#     — `POST /write?db=mydb` accepts
#     Line Protocol bytes.  Drop-in
#     replacement for InfluxDB write
#     paths from Telegraf, InfluxDB
#     SDKs, etc.
#   - HIVE PARTITIONING — data written
#     as `/{db}/{table}/date=YYYY-MM-
#     DD/hour=HH/{uuid}.{level}.
#     parquet` with `metadata.json`
#     sidecar.  Compatible with any
#     Parquet reader (Polars, PyArrow,
#     Spark)
#   - PROGRESSIVE COMPACTION — files are
#     promoted through merge levels
#     (`.1` → `.2` → `.3` → `.3`-stay)
#     at increasing frequencies (10s,
#     100s, 1000s) up to a 4 GB
#     ceiling.  Newer / hotter data
#     stays in smaller files for
#     faster ingest; older data
#     compacted into bigger files for
#     faster scans
#   - DATA LAYER MODEL — multiple
#     `GIGAPI_LAYER_<N>_*` envs let you
#     define tiered storage: hot data
#     on local SSD, warm on regional
#     S3, cold on Glacier.  TTL per
#     layer auto-rotates data
#   - SCHEMA-ON-WRITE — new columns
#     materialize automatically per
#     row.  Readers reconcile across
#     schema versions transparently
#   - EXECUTION MODES — `GIGAPI_MODE`
#     env selects:
#       * `aio` (DEFAULT) — all roles
#         in one process
#       * `readonly` — query-only node
#       * `writeonly` — ingest-only
#         node
#       * `compaction` — merge-only
#         worker
#     Scale horizontally by running
#     specialised workers
#   - METADATA TYPES —
#     `GIGAPI_METADATA_TYPE=json`
#     stores catalog in local JSON
#     files (single-node setup).
#     `=redis` shares catalog across
#     a cluster of GigAPI nodes via
#     a Redis connection at
#     `GIGAPI_METADATA_URL=redis://
#     redis:6379/0`
#   - EMBEDDED UI — `GIGAPI_UI=true`
#     (default) serves an embedded
#     web SQL workbench at the same
#     HTTP port
#
# ENVIRONMENT-DRIVEN CLI — gigapi is
# configured PURELY via environment
# variables.  The binary takes an optional
# positional argument for an INI/YAML
# config path; otherwise reads from env.
# This makes it deployment-platform-
# friendly (Docker / Kubernetes /
# systemd) but the local CLI flag
# surface is minimal
#
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (per upstream
# README table):
#   * `GIGAPI_ROOT`              root data
#                                directory
#   * `GIGAPI_MERGE_TIMEOUT_S`   base merge
#                                interval
#                                (default
#                                10)
#   * `GIGAPI_SAVE_TIMEOUT_S`    disk-flush
#                                interval
#                                (default
#                                1)
#   * `GIGAPI_NO_MERGES`         disable
#                                compaction
#   * `GIGAPI_UI`                enable
#                                embedded
#                                web UI
#                                (default
#                                true)
#   * `GIGAPI_MODE`              `aio` /
#                                `readonly` /
#                                `writeonly` /
#                                `compaction`
#   * `GIGAPI_METADATA_TYPE`     `json` /
#                                `redis`
#   * `GIGAPI_METADATA_URL`      Redis URL
#                                when type
#                                is redis
#   * `HTTP_PORT`                HTTP port
#                                (default
#                                7971)
#   * `HTTP_HOST`                HTTP bind
#                                (default
#                                0.0.0.0)
#   * `HTTP_BASIC_AUTH_USERNAME` basic auth
#                                user
#   * `HTTP_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD` basic auth
#                                password
#   * `FLIGHTSQL_PORT`           FlightSQL
#                                gRPC port
#                                (default
#                                8082)
#   * `FLIGHTSQL_ENABLE`         enable
#                                FlightSQL
#                                gRPC server
#                                (default
#                                true)
#   * `LOGLEVEL`                 debug /
#                                info /
#                                warn /
#                                error /
#                                fatal
#   * `DUCKDB_MEM_LIMIT`         DuckDB
#                                memory limit
#                                (default
#                                "1GB")
#   * `DUCKDB_THREAD_LIMIT`      DuckDB
#                                threads
#                                (default 1)
#   * `GIGAPI_LAYER_<N>_NAME`    per-layer
#                                unique name
#   * `GIGAPI_LAYER_<N>_TYPE`    `fs` or
#                                `s3`
#   * `GIGAPI_LAYER_<N>_GLOBAL`  cluster-
#                                wide
#                                accessible
#   * `GIGAPI_LAYER_<N>_URL`     path or
#                                S3 URL
#   * `GIGAPI_LAYER_<N>_TTL`     TTL before
#                                rotation
#                                (default 0
#                                = no
#                                rotation)
#
# CRITICAL DIRECT DEPENDENCIES (from
# go.mod):
#   - github.com/apache/arrow-go/v18 v18.3.0
#                              — Apache Arrow
#                                Go impl
#                                [AXIS 54
#                                LIBRARY]
#   - github.com/marcboeker/go-duckdb/v2 v2.2.0
#                              — DuckDB Go
#                                bindings
#                                (query
#                                engine)
#   - github.com/influxdata/influxdb v1.12.0
#                              — InfluxDB
#                                Line Protocol
#                                parser
#   - github.com/minio/minio-go/v7 v7.0.91
#                              — S3-
#                                compatible
#                                object
#                                storage
#                                client
#   - github.com/gigapi/gigapi-config v0.0.9
#                              — env-var
#                                config
#                                loader
#                                (sibling
#                                project)
#   - github.com/gigapi/gigapi-querier v0.0.27
#                              — DuckDB
#                                query
#                                planner
#                                (sibling
#                                project)
#   - github.com/gigapi/metadata v0.0.6
#                              — metadata
#                                catalog
#                                (JSON +
#                                Redis
#                                backends)
#   - github.com/expr-lang/expr v1.17.2
#                              — expression
#                                eval (for
#                                config
#                                templating)
#   - github.com/go-faster/city v1.0.1
#                              — CityHash
#                                for
#                                Parquet
#                                row-group
#                                IDs
#   - github.com/go-faster/jx v1.1.0
#                              — fast JSON
#                                encoder/
#                                decoder
#   - github.com/gorilla/mux v1.8.1
#                              — HTTP
#                                router
#   - github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0
#                              — UUID for
#                                Parquet
#                                file names
#   - github.com/spf13/afero v1.12.0
#                              — virtual
#                                filesystem
#                                abstraction
#
# Go 1.24.2+ MSRV per go.mod `go 1.24.2`.
#
# UPSTREAM:
#   * Source             : https://github.com/gigapi/gigapi
#   * Site               : https://gigapi.io
#   * Architecture doc   : https://github.com/gigapi/gigapi/blob/main/ARCHITECTURE.md
#   * Benchmarks         : https://github.com/gigapi/gigapi/blob/main/BENCHMARK.md
#   * apache/arrow-go    : https://github.com/apache/arrow-go
#   * License            : MIT
#   * Maintainer         : gigapi org
#
# INSTALL:
#   # From source
#   git clone https://github.com/gigapi/gigapi
#   cd gigapi
#   go build -o gigapi .
#
#   # Docker (the recommended deployment)
#   docker pull ghcr.io/gigapi/gigapi:latest
#
#   # Docker Compose (per upstream README)
#   #   services:
#   #     gigapi:
#   #       image: ghcr.io/gigapi/gigapi:latest
#   #       ports: ["7971:7971"]
#   #       environment:
#   #         - GIGAPI_ROOT=/data
#   #         - GIGAPI_LAYER_0_NAME=default
#   #         - GIGAPI_LAYER_0_TYPE=fs
#   #         - GIGAPI_LAYER_0_URL=file:///data
#
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
#
#   # Run with env-var-only config (most
#   # common deployment)
#   GIGAPI_ROOT=/data \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_NAME=default \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_TYPE=fs \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_URL=file:///data \
#       gigapi
#
#   # Run with custom HTTP port + DuckDB
#   # memory budget
#   HTTP_PORT=9090 \
#   DUCKDB_MEM_LIMIT=8GB \
#   DUCKDB_THREAD_LIMIT=8 \
#       gigapi
#
#   # Run in read-only mode (query-only node
#   # for horizontal scale-out)
#   GIGAPI_MODE=readonly \
#       gigapi
#
#   # Run in compaction-only mode (background
#   # merge worker, no HTTP/Flight serving)
#   GIGAPI_MODE=compaction \
#       gigapi
#
#   # Distributed metadata catalog via Redis
#   GIGAPI_METADATA_TYPE=redis \
#   GIGAPI_METADATA_URL=redis://redis:6379/0 \
#       gigapi
#
#   # S3 storage layer
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_TYPE=s3 \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_URL='s3://bucket-name/prefix?region=us-west-2&access_key=AKIA...&secret_key=...' \
#       gigapi
#
#   # Two-tier hot/cold storage with TTL
#   # rotation
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_NAME=hot \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_TYPE=fs \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_URL=file:///mnt/ssd \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_0_TTL=3600 \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_1_NAME=cold \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_1_TYPE=s3 \
#   GIGAPI_LAYER_1_URL='s3://bucket/archive' \
#       gigapi
#
#   # Disable embedded UI (smaller binary
#   # footprint in production)
#   GIGAPI_UI=false gigapi
#
#   # Verbose logging
#   LOGLEVEL=debug gigapi
#
# CLIENT USAGE (after gigapi is running):
#
#   # Write data via InfluxDB Line Protocol
#   cat <<EOF | curl -X POST \
#       'http://localhost:7971/write?db=mydb' \
#       --data-binary @/dev/stdin
#   weather,location=us-midwest,season=summer temperature=82
#   weather,location=us-east,season=summer temperature=80
#   weather,location=us-west,season=summer temperature=99
#   EOF
#
#   # Query via HTTP DuckDB SQL
#   curl -X POST 'http://localhost:7971/query?db=mydb' \
#       -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
#       -d '{"query":"SELECT count(*), avg(temperature) FROM weather"}'
#
#   # Query via FlightSQL (Python)
#   from flightsql import connect, FlightSQLClient
#   client = FlightSQLClient(host='localhost', port=8082,
#                            insecure=True)
#   conn = connect(client)
#   cursor = conn.cursor()
#   cursor.execute('SELECT count(*), avg(temperature) FROM weather')
#   print([r for r in cursor])
#
# OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/gigapi/gigapi/blob/main/main.go + README env-var table):
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

_arguments -C \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '1::config file:_files -g "*.(yaml|yml|ini|toml|conf)"' \
    && ret=0

return ret
